Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The MMR vaccine is very safe and effective. CDC recommends that children receive 2 doses of MMR vaccine, starting with the 1st dose at 12 through 15 months of age, and the 2nd dose at 4 through 6 years of age. Two doses of MMR vaccine are about 97 percent effective at preventing measles; 1 dose is about 93 percent effective. - Mod.LK]

