South America
-------------
[3] Venezuela (Bolivar state)
Date: Sat 11 Nov 2017
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/measles-outbreak-strikes-bolivar-state-venezuela-36809/


First it was malaria and diphtheria, now there is a measles outbreak in Venezuela's Bolivar state. According to the Pan American Health Organization (PAHO), between the last week of August [2017] and the 1st of October [2017], Bolivar State reported 570 cases of measles, specifically in 9 parishes of the Caroní municipality, of which 217 are fully confirmed. In the month of September [2017] alone, 300 cases were reported in Caroní.

Endocrinologist and member of the Venezuelan Endocrinology and Metabolism Society, Marcos Lima Martínez said, "we have not seen the preventive measures to contain the outbreak of measles," and explained that according to PAHO "76 percent of those affected in the state of Bolivar are children under 1 year of age", so on the recommendation of international health organizations the call to the population that has children with more than 6 months without receiving the trivalent viral vaccine go to the nearest ambulatory for immunization.

