Europe
------
[4] Greece and other European countries
Date: Sat 11 Nov 2017
Source: DG Alerts from European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control [edited]
http://dgalerts.docguide.com/europe-update-measles-high-incidence-greece?nl_ref=newsletter&pk_campaign=newsletter


Measles outbreaks continue to occur in a number of EU/EEA countries. There is a decreasing trend of measles cases in Italy and Romania. Greece continues reporting a substantial number of cases, particularly in the south of the country.

According to national public health authorities, measles has caused 46 deaths in EU countries in 2016 and 2017. In 2016, 12 deaths occurred in Romania and one in the UK. In 2017, 33 deaths were reported from Romania (23), Italy (4), Bulgaria (1), Germany (1), Portugal (1), France (1), Greece (1) and Spain (1). All EU/EEA countries have reported measles cases in 2017, except for Latvia, Liechtenstein and Malta.

In the latest Communicable Disease Threat Report published by the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control on [Sat 11 Nov 2017], updates are provided for Austria, Germany, Greece, Ireland, Italy, Romania, Spain and the UK as follows:

- Austria has reported 1 case since the previous update on 13 Oct 2017. In 2017, as of 25 October, Austria reported 85 cases. This exceeds the number of measles cases in 2016.

- Germany has reported 7 cases since the previous report on 13 Oct 2017. In 2017, as of 15 Oct, Germany reported 898 cases. During the same time period in 2016, Germany reported 273 cases.

- Greece has reported 153 cases since the previous report on 13 Oct 2017, including 1 death which has been reported in an unvaccinated 11-month infant. Between 17 May and 29 Oct 2017, Greece reported 368 cases, with a higher incidence in southern Greece. Most cases were children 1--9 years old, followed by adults 25--44 years old, unvaccinated or incompletely vaccinated.

- Ireland has reported 7 cases since the previous report on 8 Sep 2017. In 2017, as of 28 Oct, Ireland has reported 16 cases. During the same period in 2016, Ireland reported 43 cases.

- Italy has reported 158 cases since the previous report on 13 Oct 2017. In 2017, as of 31 Oct, Italy has reported 4775 cases, including 4 deaths. Of these cases, 312 are healthcare workers. The median age is 27 years; 88 percent of the cases were not vaccinated and 6 percent received only 1 dose of vaccine. In 2016, Italy reported 862 cases during the year.

- Romania has reported 189 cases and 1 death since the previous report on 13 Oct 2017. Since 1 Jan 2016 and as of 3 Nov 2017, Romania has reported 9728 cases, including 35 deaths. Of these, 1969 cases were reported in 2016 and 7759 cases were reported in 2017.

- Spain has reported 159 cases in 2017 as of 27 October. In 2016, Spain reported 38 cases during the year.

- The UK: Media report a measles outbreak with over 30 cases in Gloucestershire, South West England, with over 20 cases in one school.

